---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import styles from '../styles/how-to.module.css';
---

<Layout title="How to Use Shimmr" description="Learn how to get the most out of Shimmr.">
  <div class={styles.howToContainer}>
    <div class={styles.section}>
      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>1</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Find a safe, calm space</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Before starting a session, make sure you're in a quiet, relaxed place. Avoid using Shimmr
          while driving or operating machinery. The brain may enter altered states of consciousness,
          so safety first.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>2</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Use stereo headphones</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Binaural beats require separate tones in each ear to work. Use quality stereo headphones —
          wireless or wired — for the full effect. Earbuds work too, but over-ear headphones usually
          offer deeper immersion.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>3</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Set the right volume</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Keep the volume low to medium — loud volumes can distract or reduce the entrainment
          effect. Aim for a comfortable level where the sound feels immersive but gentle.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>4</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Explore and choose your sound</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Sounds are grouped by goals, moods, and categories. Use the search bar to enter keywords
          like "focus" or "relax." Read the short descriptions to find presets that match your
          intention.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>5</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Set the session duration</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Use the timer on the play screen to choose how long you want to listen. A minimum of 5–10
          minutes is recommended for noticeable effects, but longer sessions (20–30+ minutes) often
          work best for deep states.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>6</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Use with other apps</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Enable the "Play with other apps" toggle in Settings. This lets Shimmr continue in the
          background while you use other apps — great for reading, journaling, or watching calming
          visuals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>7</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Track your sessions with HealthKit</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          If connected, Shimmr saves sessions over 1 minute to Apple Health. You can track your
          consistency, daily minutes, and progress toward wellness goals over time.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>8</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Fine-tune your audio experience</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Open the audio mixer from the play screen to adjust individual sound elements — like
          ambient layers, tones, or background textures. You can also set reverb and EQ for a
          polished final sound. This is perfect for crafting your own vibe or enhancing comfort for
          headphones.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class={styles.step}>
        <h3>
          <span class={styles.stepNumber}>9</span>
          <span class={styles.stepTitle}>Use regularly</span>
        </h3>
        <p>
          Consistency matters. Using Shimmr daily — even for just a few minutes — can help train
          your brain, improve mood, and support focus or relaxation over time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
